      {
        "id": "OaMcRjmrPwlxilaS",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>What is a good estimate for the total cost of the four items?</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILEmW3XoZOoVI1_",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary.</p><p>Notepad about $9</p><p>Markers about $7</p><p>Pencils about $4</p><p>Sticky Notes about $4</p><p>$9 + $7 + $4 + $4 = $24</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "I46ZJG0JviVxnVnU",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>What is a good estimate for the total bill with tax?</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILEM0xAb4--JSyH",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary.</p><p>Using the above estimate of $24, many students will find 5% of 24 and then add that amount into the original $24.</p><p>  0.05 x 24 = $1.2</p><p>  24 + 1.2 = $25.20</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "_dNaZZOHhg6BJI3a",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Does Skylar have enough money?  Explain your reasoning.</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILE2D12EnlW7BgG",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary.</p><p>Using the above estimates students might say yes because we overestimated most of the prices and with our estimate being only $0.20 over the $25, he should have enough money. Others might say no because our estimate is over the $25. Students should be able to describe how they estimated and whether they used overestimates or underestimates.</p>"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
